rComments: Be ready to work hard. The course is fun, Prof. is amazing but you need to invest time. I found the exams on the hard side but not like impossible. You need to attend the lectures. The Prof. explains all very well and very responsive and helpful to studnets.

Besides being very knowledgeable and technical, Professor Kantarci is a very inspiring, encouraging, and helpful person which you don't see very much these days. He has a great group of grad students with great projects at hand. You will consider yourself lucky if you get the chance to work under his supervision. He is simply the best person.

I'm on an internship this semester and I got through the interview from what i learned in this course. The prof has a great personality, very respectful to students and answers questions in depth not just swishes away like some other profs.

The prof used a book called Introduction to Machine learning for his lectures, which were recorded in advance and posted online. He LITERALLY read the book for his lectures Didnt even come up with his own examples! We know how to read English btw! He tried to avoid any live sessions with us so he doesnt get any questions that embarrass him
Avoid this subject if possible. We ended up learning almost nothing. However, the professor very kind and lenient.
I wish you could give 0. This prof is probably the worst at Uottawa. Incomplete notes and exams have nothing to do with the notes. AVOID.

He seems to know the stuff he is teaching but actually he doesn't. He just pretends to be an expert but with one deep conversation you will find out that he's not really good enough. Also, the students working with him in the grad level complain a lot of him being so unprofessional, so I recommend that you dont go with for a master/PhD.

The course was interesting, and he was a decent lecturer. He really knows his stuff, so if you have questions, definitely ask during class. It's a 4th-year course, but it was so easy that a high school student could do well in it.
assignments were tough but graded easy
